PARTY

Syntax: party form <name>
        party join <name>
        party add <player>
        party remove <player>
        party leader <player>
        party leave
        party list

Forms or manages a party: a group of players who share experience
based on relative level when they fight together. The player who
forms a party is its leader; only the leader may add, remove, or
transfer leadership.

Party membership has no chat line of its own. To talk with party
members who are not in your room, use tell (private, one-to-one) or
agree on a radio frequency and use a carried radio.

See also: follow, kill, radio, tell
